Package: cprime
Version: 0.1.0-alpha
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.17), libssl3, libcurl4, libjson-c5, libreadline8
Recommends: build-essential, nasm, code
Suggests: valgrind, gdb
Installed-Size: 1428
Maintainer: C-Prime Project <cprime@proton.me>
Description: C-Prime programming language compiler and tools
 C-Prime (C`) is a statically typed, memory-safe systems programming
 language that combines C's simplicity with Rust-style borrow checking.
 The ` (backtick) operator is the borrow operator.
 .
 This package includes:
  * cpc  -- C-Prime Compiler (compiles .cp files to native Linux binaries)
  * cpg  -- C-Prime Guard (memory safety and vulnerability analyzer)
  * cppm -- C-Prime Package Manager (install packages, check for updates)
 .
 cppm appears in your application menu under Development.
 Install the VS Code extension (.vslnx) for syntax highlighting and tutorials.
Homepage: https://github.com/cprime-lang/cprime
